<div class="wrapper">
    <p style="text-align: center;">Welcome to the documentation for Lilia.</p>
    <p>This is a basic skeleton that serves as a raw foundation for building any schema according to a player's preferences. It provides a starting point with essential functionalities and can be expanded upon to create custom gameplay experiences.</p>
    <p>To utilize this schema, ensure you have the <a href="https://github.com/LiliaFramework/Lilia" target="_blank">Lilia framework</a> installed.</p>

    <h2>Developers</h2>
    <p>The sidebar displays the entire contents of the documentation for this schema. They are all searchable with the search box at the top of the sidebar.

    <h2>Server Owners</h2>
    <p>If you're looking to get your server up and running as soon as possible, check out the <a href="https://liliaframework.github.io/manual/info_installation/" target="_blank">Installation Tutorial</a> guide in the manual. Remember that this schema is dependent on the <a href="https://github.com/LiliaFramework/Lilia" target="_blank">Lilia framework</a>.</p>
